---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBar from "../components/NavBar.svelte";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="ScrapNet"
	description="ScrapNet is an open, licence-friendly library of printable gadgets, firmware, and prompt packs."
>
	<NavBar />

	<a href="#main" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only p-4">Skip to main content</a>

	<main
		id="main"
		class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-[4.5rem] space-y-16"
	>
		<!-- Hero -->
		<section class="text-center">
			<img src="/logo.png" alt="ScrapNet logo" class="mx-auto w-12 h-12" />
			<h1 class="font-mono text-5xl sm:text-6xl mt-4">ScrapNet</h1>
			<p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg">
				A public library of printable hardware designs, firmware, and prompt
				packs—shared without paywalls or ranking boards.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- What is ScrapNet? -->
		<section id="about" class="space-y-4">
			<h2 class="font-mono text-3xl">What&nbsp;is&nbsp;ScrapNet?</h2>
			<p>
				ScrapNet hosts raw files—STLs, schematics, firmware builds, and prompt
				snippets—in one permissively licensed catalogue. Anyone can download,
				print, flash, or remix without requesting access or handing over
				personal data.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- Thesis Prototype -->
		<section id="prototype" class="space-y-4">
			<h2 class="font-mono text-3xl">Thesis Prototype: BLE Button</h2>

			<p>The first reference gadget illustrates the entire ScrapNet flow:</p>

			<ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
				<li>
					<strong>Housing —</strong> 3-D-printable case, coin-cell powered.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Electronics —</strong> off-the-shelf BLE module with open firmware.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Mobile bridge —</strong> beta Android app (Play Store closed test).
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>BYOK —</strong> button events forwarded to <u
						>any cloud AI API</u
					> you configure (OpenAI, Claude, etc.).
				</li>
			</ul>

			<p>Suggested default press patterns (fully editable in firmware):</p>
			<ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
				<li><strong>Single press —</strong> begin voice query.</li>
				<li><strong>Double press —</strong> stop response early.</li>
				<li><strong>Long press —</strong> clear context.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<!-- Roadmap -->
		<section id="roadmap" class="space-y-4">
			<h2 class="font-mono text-3xl">Next&nbsp;Milestones</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
				<li>
					Publish STL, schematic &amp; firmware for the BLE button — Q4 2025
				</li>
				<li>Release Android relay app (closed beta → public APK)</li>
				<li>
					Open catalogue for additional printable tools &amp; prompt packs
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<!-- Footer note -->
		<section class="text-center text-sm italic">
			This page will grow the moment the first files are live. No accounts, no
			cookies—just downloads.
		</section>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
